# Evidentia context & handoff protocol

Evidentia is a persona-aware documentation agent: a Next.js frontend + a Python
FastAPI multi-agent backend that turns enterprise docs into cited, role-specific
playbooks. The pipeline is **deterministic-first**; LLM usage is optional and
only refines the deterministic baseline.

## Always, before substantial work

1. Read `docs/ai/PROJECT_STATE.md` (current status, LLM modes, latest benchmark, tests).
2. Read `docs/ai/SESSION_HANDOFF.md` (most recent changes, open concerns, next steps).

Consult `docs/ai/ARCHITECTURE.md` for the stable design and
`docs/ai/DECISIONS.md` for rationale. Root `AGENTS.md` has commands and guardrails.

## Always, after meaningful implementation

Update the documentation so the next agent can continue:
- `docs/ai/PROJECT_STATE.md` — refresh the snapshot; keep it concise.
- `docs/ai/SESSION_HANDOFF.md` — rewrite for the new state; keep it under 100 lines.
- `docs/ai/DECISIONS.md` — append a new dated entry (append-only; do not edit past ones).
- `docs/ai/ARCHITECTURE.md` — only if the stable design changed.

## Non-negotiables

- Never commit secrets. `backend/.env` is local + git-ignored; keys live only there.
- Do not break the public `EvidentiaReport` schema (additive optional fields only).
- Preserve the deterministic fallback (works with no LLM key and no backend).
- Run backend `python -m pytest -q` and frontend `npm run build` before finishing.
